Abstraction:
    - Hiding the internal implementation by providing functionality to the user.
    - It is the pillar which help us to build the interface or architecture/ design to build a useful product.
    - To perform abstraction three things are required:
        -> Abstract class :
            - It is a class which should contain atleast one abstract method inside it.
            - Abstract class should be the child class of ABC(Abstract Base class) class.
            - ABC class is present in abc module.
            - We cannot create object for abstract class.
        -> Abstract method :
            - It is a method which is declared without any implementation.
            - It is defined with @abstractmethod decorator.
            - @abstractmethod decorator is present in abc module.
        -> Concrete class :
            - It is a class which is the child class of abstract class.
            - It is responsible to provide implementation for all the abstract method present in the abstract class.
            - We can create object for concrete class.

    - Syntax:
        from abc import ABC, abstractmethod

        class AbstractClassName(ABC):
            @abstractmethod
            def abstract_method_name(self):
                pass

        class ConcreteClassName(AbstractClassName):
            def abstract_method_name(self):
                # implementation of abstract method
                